{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c9f32392-f1d7-4442-9cb8-bdd91d16db35","content":"I don't see a `.dmp` file in the current directory. Could you provide the path to it?\n\nIn the meantime, here's how to analyze it once we have it:\n\n### Recommended tool: `dotnet-dump`\n\n**Install it:**\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n```\n\n**Analyze the dump:**\n```bash\ndotnet-dump analyze /path/to/your.dmp\n```\n\n**Key commands inside the analyzer:**\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `clrstack` | Managed call stack of current thread |\n| `pe` (PrintException) | Show last exception details |\n| `dumpheap -stat` | Heap summary (for memory issues) |\n| `threads` | List all threads |\n| `setthread <id>` | Switch to a specific thread |\n| `clrstack -all` | Stacks for all threads |\n\n**Typical workflow to find a crash root cause:**\n1. Run `pe` to check for an unhandled exception\n2. Run `threads` to find the faulting thread\n3. Run `clrstack` to see the managed call stack\n\nDrop the `.dmp` file here or give me its path, and I'll walk through the analysis with you.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8dfa856b-16ac-4671-b07f-99b81aeba47b","outputTokens":296,"requestId":"D813:14859A:35226CA:3A2DD22:69FBF174"},"id":"5a4796e4-e2b8-42f7-bb19-8ffc5e24f25a","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:57:17.115Z","parentId":"cc0f0c9f-9c31-4742-9f0e-a4efda4468e2"}
